administered to promote urine alkalization and renal protection. The patient&#x2019;s myoglobin
(acute phase muscle injury marker) level reduced gradually, there was a sudden and
transient elevation in the total CPK level followed by a gradual decrease in the level,
as expected in cases of rhabdomyolysis with a benign course (<xref ref-type="table" rid="t02">Table 2</xref>).</p>
